The paper deals with optimization of transmission protocols and network-wide spectral efficiency in a cellular network, which involves multiple-input-multiple-output (MIMO) and orthogonal frequency-division multiple-access (OFDMA) technologies. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also addresses power control variables and system constraints, which are relevant to control and systems engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of spatial multiplexing components (SMCs) and grouping algorithms suggests a focus on multimedia systems (cs.MM) and communication networks (cs.COM).
